  "narration": [
    {
      "timestamp": 0,
      "speaker": "narrator",
      "text": "In 1219, following the Otrar massacre where Khwarezmian forces killed Mongol envoys, Genghis Khan assembled a massive army of approximately 200,000 soldiers.",
      "citationUrls": ["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mongol_conquest_of_the_Khwarazmian_Empire"]
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 15,
      "speaker": "narrator",
      "text": "The Mongol army departed from Karakorum, crossing thousands of miles of steppes and deserts toward the Khwarezmian Empire.",
      "citationUrls": ["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mongol_invasion_of_Khwarezmia"]
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 60,
      "speaker": "narrator",
      "text": "In autumn 1219, the Mongols reached Otrar, the city where the massacre occurred. The siege would last five months.",
      "citationUrls": ["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siege_of_Otrar"]
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 70,
      "speaker": "narrator",
      "text": "Otrar fell in February 1220. The governor Inalchuq, who ordered the massacre, was executed by having molten silver poured into his eyes and ears.",
      "citationUrls": ["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siege_of_Otrar"]
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 78,
      "speaker": "narrator",
      "text": "Genghis Khan personally led the assault on Bukhara, one of the great cultural centers of the Islamic world. The city surrendered after a brief siege in March 1220.",
      "citationUrls": ["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siege_of_Bukhara"]
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 88,
      "speaker": "narrator",
      "text": "In June 1220, the Mongols reached Samarkand, the capital of the Khwarezmian Empire. Despite having 100,000 defenders, the city fell after just five days.",
      "citationUrls": ["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Siege_of_Samarkand_(1220)"]
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 100,
      "speaker": "narrator",
      "text": "By 1221, the Khwarezmian Empire had effectively ceased to exist. The Mongol Empire now stretched from the Pacific to the Caspian Sea.",
      "citationUrls": ["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mongol_conquest_of_the_Khwarazmian_Empire"]
    }
  ],
